import plotly.graph_objects as go
import yfinance as yf

# List of tickers to include
tickers = ['AAPL', 'TSLA', 'GOOGL', 'AMZN', 'MSFT']
data_dict = {}

# Download data for each ticker and rename columns
for ticker in tickers:
    df = yf.download(ticker, start='2020-01-01', end='2024-12-31')
    df.columns = ['Close', 'High', 'Low', 'Open', 'Volume']  # flatten like before
    data_dict[ticker] = df

# Initialize figure
fig = go.Figure()

# Add one trace per ticker, but only show the first one
for i, ticker in enumerate(tickers):
    visible = True if i == 0 else False
    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
        x=data_dict[ticker].index,
        y=data_dict[ticker]['Close'],
        mode='lines',
        name=f'{ticker} Close',
        visible=visible
    ))

# Create dropdown buttons
buttons = []
for i, ticker in enumerate(tickers):
    vis = [False] * len(tickers)
    vis[i] = True
    buttons.append(dict(label=ticker,
                        method='update',
                        args=[{'visible': vis},
                              {'title': f'{ticker} Stock Closing Price (20202024)'}]))

# Update layout with dropdown
fig.update_layout(
    updatemenus=[dict(
        active=0,
        buttons=buttons,
        x=0.05,
        xanchor='left',
        y=1.15,
        yanchor='top'
    )],
    title='AAPL Stock Closing Price (20202024)',
    xaxis_title='Date',
    yaxis_title='Price (USD)',
    template='plotly_white',
    width=1000,
    height=500
)

fig.show()

In[17]:
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import yfinance as yf
import pandas as pd

# List of tickers
tickers = ['AAPL', 'TSLA', 'GOOGL', 'AMZN', 'MSFT']
data_dict = {}

# Download and prepare data
for ticker in tickers:
    df = yf.download(ticker, start='2020-01-01', end='2024-12-31')
    df.columns = ['Close', 'High', 'Low', 'Open', 'Volume']
    df['MA30'] = df['Close'].rolling(window=30).mean()
    data_dict[ticker] = df

# Create subplots: 2 rows (price + MA, volume)
fig = go.Figure()

# Add traces for each ticker
for i, ticker in enumerate(tickers):
    df = data_dict[ticker]
    visible = i == 0  # Only show first by default

    # Price Line
    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
        x=df.index,
        y=df['Close'],
        mode='lines',
        name=f'{ticker} Close',
        visible=visible,
        line=dict(color='blue')
    ))

    # 30-day Moving Average
    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
        x=df.index,
        y=df['MA30'],
        mode='lines',
        name=f'{ticker} MA30',
        visible=visible,
        line=dict(color='orange', dash='dash')
    ))

    # Volume (secondar chart)
    fig.add_trace(go.Bar(
        x=df.index,
        y=df['Volume'],
        name=f'{ticker} Volume',
        visible=visible,
        marker=dict(color='rgba(128,128,128,0.5)')
    ))

In[18]:
# Create dropdown buttons
buttons = []
for i, ticker in enumerate(tickers):
    vis = [False] * (len(tickers) * 3)
    vis[i * 3] = True       # Close
    vis[i * 3 + 1] = True   # MA30
    vis[i * 3 + 2] = True   # Volume

    buttons.append(dict(label=ticker,
                        method='update',
                        args=[{'visible': vis},
                              {'title': f'{ticker} Stock Price, MA30 & Volume (20202024)'}]))

# Update layout
fig.update_layout(
    updatemenus=[dict(
        active=0,
        buttons=buttons,
        x=0.05,
        xanchor='left',
        y=1.2,
        yanchor='top'
    )],
    title='AAPL Stock Price, MA30 & Volume (20202024)',
    xaxis=dict(title='Date'),
    yaxis=dict(title='Price (USD)', domain=[0.35, 1]),
    yaxis2=dict(title='Volume', domain=[0, 0.25]),
    template='plotly_white',
    height=700,
    width=1000,
    showlegend=True
)

# Assign y-axes to traces
for i in range(len(tickers)):
    fig.data[i * 3]['yaxis'] = 'y'    # Close
    fig.data[i * 3 + 1]['yaxis'] = 'y'  # MA30
    fig.data[i * 3 + 2]['yaxis'] = 'y2' # Volume

# Show the final dashboard
fig.show()
